cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Performance Evaluation of MoonGen and L2 Forwarder Latency under Simulated
  Network Load
abstract: This dataset documents an experiment designed to assess network latency
  performance using the MoonGen load generation tool and a libmoon L2 forwarder component.
  The methodology involved establishing controlled environments on nodes nida and
  cesis, utilizing scripts to configure DUTs and load generators with configurable
  packet rates and sizes. Per-run logs captured timing data during simulated network
  traffic through both tools, focusing on latency measurements. Evaluation outputs
  included CSV log files of latencies and associated image plots generated from the
  raw data, providing insights into system performance characteristics under varying
  workload conditions.
